I stumbled onto TJ's while walking around and it ended up being exactly what I wanted. TJ's has the perfect diner atmosphere, great prices, and plenty of coffee to wake you up on an early Sunday morning.  Other reviewers have mentioned that the food isn't great. And while yeah, that's true, it isn't bad either. It's just typical diner food in a typical diner environment. If that's what you're looking for then TJ's is great. Otherwise, fancier brunches can be had elsewhere.
